HEADWORD: Cock
<hw>Cock</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of. <ets>coque</ets>, F.
<ets>coche</ets>, a small vessel, L. <ets>concha</ets> muscle shell, a
vessel. See <er>Coach</er>, and cf. <er>Cog</er> a small boat.]</ety>
<def>A small boat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yond tall anchoring bark [appears]⟦br⟧
Diminished to her <qex>cock</qex>; her <qex>cock</qex>, a buoy⟦br⟧
